<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 02 at 6:31AM CDT  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...AREAS OF FOG ACROSS JIM HOGG AND BROOKS COUNTIES THIS
MORNING...
Surface observations show that visibilities in Hebbronville have
fallen to a quarter mile early this morning. Areas of fog are
expected to reduce visibilities to 1 mile or less at times through
the morning across portions of Jim Hogg and Brooks counties. Be
sure to drive with caution by using your low beams and allowing
plenty of space between your vehicle and the vehicle in front of
you if on the roads this morning.</description>
